    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot (with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has started to brown, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>grated carrot </strong>and <strong>chopped tomato </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>allspice</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>sumac </strong>(save some for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>with 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>sugar</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>with your <strong>sultanas</strong>, <strong>beef stock </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook for 12-15 min, covered, or until all the rice is tender and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>spiced Persian-style pilaf</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>spiced Persian-style pilaf </strong>is ready, allow to rest, covered, for 5 mins</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-persian-style-lamb-pilaf/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced Persian-style pilaf</strong></p><p>Drizzle with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining ground sumac</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
